American Ninja Warrior is a sports entertainment competition spin-off of the television series Sasuke.
The series began on December 12, 2009, in Los Angeles, with the top 10 competitors moving on to compete 
at "Mt. Midoriyama" in Japan. American Ninja Warrior succeeded G4's American Ninja Challenge as the qualifying
route for Americans to enter Sasuke.
